--- Some things to know to install mathmaker
Before there is a proper installation process

> Dependencies
Softwares used by mathmaker:
- euktoeps
Provided by package eukleides (on both Ubuntu & FreeBsd)

- xmllint
Provided by package: libxml2-utils on Ubuntu

Libraries imported by mathmaker:
- yaml
Provided by package: python3-yaml on Ubuntu

- polib
Provided by package: python3-polib on Ubuntu

> To compile mathmaker's output
- lualatex
Provided by package: texlive-luatex on Ubuntu

> Configuration
- logging for OSes using rsyslogd, like debian, Ubuntu...:
Ensure /etc/rsyslog.conf contains:
    $IncludeConfig /etc/rsyslog.d/*.conf
So, create (if not created yet) a 'local' configuration file, like:
/etc/rsyslog.d/40-local.conf
and put (or add) in it:

#  Local user rules for rsyslog.
#
#
local5.*                     /var/log/mathmaker.log

Then save it and:
# service rsyslog restart

/!\ do not create /var/log/mathmaker.log yourself with the wrong rights, otherwise nothing will be logged.

To format the messages in a nicer way, it's possible to add this in /etc/rsyslog.conf:
    $template MathmakerTpl,"%$now% %timegenerated:12:23:date-rfc3339% %syslogtag%%msg%\n"
and then, modify /etc/rsyslog.d/40-local.conf like:
    local5.*                        /var/log/mathmaker.log;MathmakerTpl
    
Tools to check everything's fine: after having restarted rsyslog:
    # rsyslogd -N1 | grep mathmaker
should show something like:
    rsyslogd: version 7.4.4, config validation run (level 1), master config /etc/rsyslog.conf
    8895.695461400:7fee0e69d780:   ACTION 0x77d3c0 [builtin:omfile:/var/log/mathmaker.log;MathmakerTpl]
    8895.699887538:7fee0e69d780:   ACTION 0x77d3c0 [builtin:omfile:/var/log/mathmaker.log;MathmakerTpl]
    rsyslogd: End of config validation run. Bye.

